{"title_page": "Haute Autorit\u00e9 pour la transparence de la vie publique", "text_new": "{{copy edit|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox government agency\n| name                = HAVP\n| full_name           = Haute Autorit\u00e9 pour la transparence de la vie publique\n| logo                = \n| formed              = {{Start date|2013|12|19}}\n| chief1_name          = Jean-Louis Nadal\n| type                = [[Governmental organization]]\n| website             = https://www.hatvp.fr/\n}}\n\nThe '''Haute Autorit\u00e9 pour la transparence de la vie publique''' ('''HATVP''') is a [[France|French]] administrative authority in-charge of ascertaining and preventing potential [[conflict of interest|conflicts of interest]] among French [[Civil service|public servants]].\n\n== History ==\nUntil 1988, the investigation and enforcement of ethical issues such as [[Conflict of interest]] or [[Cronyism]], in [[Politics of France|French politics]] fell under the [[Criminal procedure]], but there was no dedicated law or authority for dealing with such affairs.<ref>{{cite web\n| url=http://www.hatvp.fr/historique\n| archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20190814142515/http://www.hatvp.fr/historique\n| archive-date=2019-08-14\n| title=historique\n| publisher=hatvp.fr\n| accessdate=2019-12-15\n| url-status=dead\n}}</ref>\n\nThis changed after the [[Luchaire Affair|Luchaire Affair,]] which took place between 1982 and 1986. While [[Charles Hernu]] was the French [[Minister of the Armed Forces (France)|Minister of Defence]], France supplied shells to [[Iran]]. Since Iran was under an arms embargo at the time, it required the falsification of [[End-user certificate|EUC]]'s to show other destinations rather than Iran. This illegal activity was revealed by the ''Presse de la Manche'' newspaper, followed by a report of the ''Contr\u00f4le g\u00e9n\u00e9ral des arm\u00e9es'' which was published by [[L'Express]] in January 1987.<ref>{{cite web\n| url=https://www.lexpress.fr/informations/1987-l-affaire-luchaire_603634.html\n| date=1995-03-30\n| title=1987: l'affaire Luchaire \n| publisher=[[L'Express]]\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref>\n\nFollowing this scandal, the first ''transparency of public life'' law was passed: it defined the state funding of political parties and made it mandatory for some public servants to publish their financial status.<ref name=\"fnfo\">{{cite web\n| url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/replay-radio/histoires-d-info/la-transparence-de-la-vie-politique-a-marche-forcee-1988-2014_1769191.html\n| date=2015-01-06\n| title=1987: La transparence de la vie politique \u00e0 marche forc\u00e9e\n| publisher=[[France Info]]\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref> However, this was still very vague and unclear in some aspects.\n\nIn 1994, a parliamentary working group led by [[Philippe S\u00e9guin]] made 18 proposals including the limitation of election expenses, the reformation of the status of political parties, and the extension of the mandatory declaration of status to more categories of public servants.<ref name=\"fnfo\"/>\n\nOn April 10th, 2013, after the [[Cahuzac affair]], the HAVP is created.<ref>{{cite web\n| url=https://www.lejdd.fr/Politique/Actualite/Transparence-une-Haute-autorite-pour-quoi-faire-601252\n| date=2013-04-10\n| archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lejdd.fr%2FPolitique%2FActualite%2FTransparence-une-Haute-autorite-pour-quoi-faire-601252%23\n| archive-date=2014-10-27\n| title=1987: Transparence : une Haute autorit\u00e9, pour quoi faire?\n| publisher=[[Le Journal du Dimanche]]\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref>\n\n==Missions==\nThe main missions of the HATVP are:<ref>{{cite web\n| url=https://www.hatvp.fr/la-haute-autorite/#\n| title=La haute Autorit\u00e9\n| publisher=hatvp.fr\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref>\n* Preventing conflicts of interest for key public servants\n* Inspecting any significant changes to the net assets of public servants during their service (as an anti-fraud measure)\n* Inspecting faulty or fraudulent declarations of Conflict of Interest or assets of public servants\n* Overseeing \"[[Revolving door (politics)|revolving door]]\" behaviors among former and present public servants\n* Overseeing [[Lobbying]]\n\n==Composition==\nThe HAVP is composed of:<ref>{{cite web\n| url=https://www.hatvp.fr/la-haute-autorite/linstitution/organisation/\n| title=Organisation\n| publisher=hatvp.fr\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref>\n* A president\n* Two members elected by the [[Conseil d'\u00c9tat (France)|Conseil d'\u00c9tat]]\n* Two members elected by the [[Court of Audit (France)|Court of Audit]]\n* One member nominated by the president of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]]\n* One member nominated by the president of the [[Senate (France)|Senate]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|https://www.hatvp.fr/}}\n\n[[Category:Government of France]]\n", "text_old": "{{copy edit|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox government agency\n| name                = HAVP\n| full_name           = Haute Autorit\u00e9 pour la transparence de la vie publique\n| logo                = \n| formed              = {{Start date|2013|12|19}}\n| chief1_name          = Jean-Louis Nadal\n| type                = [[Governmental organization]]\n| website             = https://www.hatvp.fr/\n}}\n\nThe '''Haute Autorit\u00e9 pour la transparence de la vie publique''' ('''HATVP''') is a [[France|French]] administrative authority in-charge of ascertaining and preventing potential [[conflict of interest|conflicts of interest]] among French [[Civil service|public servants]].\n\n== History ==\nUntil 1988, the investigation and enforcement of ethical problems such as [[Conflict of interest]] or [[Cronyism]], in the [[Politics of France|French politics]] fell under the [[Criminal procedure]], but there was no dedicated law or authority for dealing with such affairs.<ref>{{cite web\n| url=http://www.hatvp.fr/historique\n| archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20190814142515/http://www.hatvp.fr/historique\n| archive-date=2019-08-14\n| title=historique\n| publisher=hatvp.fr\n| accessdate=2019-12-15\n| url-status=dead\n}}</ref>\n\nThis changed after the [[Luchaire Affair|Luchaire Affair,]] which took place between 1982 and 1986. While [[Charles Hernu]] was the French [[Minister of the Armed Forces (France)|Minister of Defence]], France supplied shells to [[Iran]]. Since Iran was under an arms embargo at the time, it required the falsification of [[End-user certificate|EUC]]'s to show other destinations rather than Iran. This illegal activity was revealed by the ''Presse de la Manche'' newspaper, followed by a report of the ''Contr\u00f4le g\u00e9n\u00e9ral des arm\u00e9es'' which was published by [[L'Express]] in January 1987.<ref>{{cite web\n| url=https://www.lexpress.fr/informations/1987-l-affaire-luchaire_603634.html\n| date=1995-03-30\n| title=1987: l'affaire Luchaire \n| publisher=[[L'Express]]\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref>\n\nFollowing this scandal, the first ''transparency of public life'' law was voted: it defined the state funding of political parties and made it mandatory for some public servants to publish their financial status.<ref name=\"fnfo\">{{cite web\n| url=https://www.francetvinfo.fr/replay-radio/histoires-d-info/la-transparence-de-la-vie-politique-a-marche-forcee-1988-2014_1769191.html\n| date=2015-01-06\n| title=1987: La transparence de la vie politique \u00e0 marche forc\u00e9e\n| publisher=[[France Info]]\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref> However, this was still very vague and unclear in some aspects.\n\nIn 1994, a parliamentary working group led by [[Philippe S\u00e9guin]] made 18 proposals including the limitation of election expenses and a reform of the status of political parties and the extension of the mandatory declaration of status to more categories of public servants.<ref name=\"fnfo\"/>\n\nOn April 10th, 2013, after the [[Cahuzac affair]], the HAVP is created.<ref>{{cite web\n| url=https://www.lejdd.fr/Politique/Actualite/Transparence-une-Haute-autorite-pour-quoi-faire-601252\n| date=2013-04-10\n| archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lejdd.fr%2FPolitique%2FActualite%2FTransparence-une-Haute-autorite-pour-quoi-faire-601252%23\n| archive-date=2014-10-27\n| title=1987: Transparence : une Haute autorit\u00e9, pour quoi faire?\n| publisher=[[Le Journal du Dimanche]]\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref>\n\n==Missions==\nThe main missions of the HATVP are:<ref>{{cite web\n| url=https://www.hatvp.fr/la-haute-autorite/#\n| title=La haute Autorit\u00e9\n| publisher=hatvp.fr\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref>\n* Preventing conflicts of interest for key public servants\n* Inspecting any significant changes to the net assets of public servants during their service (as an anti-fraud measure)\n* Inspecting faulty or fraudulent declarations of Conflict of Interest or assets of public servants\n* Overseeing \"[[Revolving door (politics)|revolving door]]\" behaviors among former and present public servants\n* Overseeing [[Lobbying]]\n\n==Composition==\nThe HAVP is composed of:<ref>{{cite web\n| url=https://www.hatvp.fr/la-haute-autorite/linstitution/organisation/\n| title=Organisation\n| publisher=hatvp.fr\n| accessdate=2019-12-15}}</ref>\n* A president\n* Two members elected by the [[Conseil d'\u00c9tat (France)|Conseil d'\u00c9tat]]\n* Two members elected by the [[Court of Audit (France)|Court of Audit]]\n* One member nominated by the president of the [[National Assembly (France)|National Assembly]]\n* One member nominated by the president of the [[Senate (France)|Senate]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|https://www.hatvp.fr/}}\n\n[[Category:Government of France]]\n", "name_user": "AprilleShowers", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHistory", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haute_Autorit%C3%A9_pour_la_transparence_de_la_vie_publique"}
{"title_page": "Alejandro Foglia", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n| name = Alejandro Foglia\n| full_name = Alejandro Jos\u00e9 Foglia Costa\n| birth_date = {{Birth-date and age|30 January 1984}}\n| birth_place = [[Montevideo]], Uruguay\n| height = 188 cm\n| weight = {{convert|13|st|kg}} \n| club = Yacht Club Punta del Este\n}}\n\n'''Alejandro Jos\u00e9 Foglia Costa'''{{efn Spanish name|Foglia|Costa}} (born 30 January 1984 in [[Montevideo]]) is a [[Uruguay]]an [[sailor]] in the [[Laser (dinghy)|Laser]] and [[Finn (dinghy)|Finn]] classes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observa.com.uy/osecciones/especiales2/nota.aspx?id=114322 |title=Alejandro Foglia |date=28 June 2008 |work=Observa |accessdate=10 July 2012 |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100421164801/http://www.observa.com.uy/osecciones/especiales2/nota.aspx?id=114322 |archivedate=21 April 2010 }}</ref>\n\nHe competed in four [[Summer Olympics]] for his native [[South America]]n country: [[Sailing at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Laser class|2004]], [[Sailing at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's Laser class|2008]], [[Sailing at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's Laser class|2012]] and [[Sailing at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Finn|2016]], and in two [[Pan American Games]]: [[Sailing at the 2007 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's Laser class|2007]] and [[Sailing at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's Laser class|2011]].\n\nHe was named Uruguay's [[flagbearer]] for the [[2008 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deportesar.terra.com.ar/pekin2008/interna/0,,OI3012303-EI10485,00.html |title=Regatista Alejandro Foglia ser\u00e1 el abanderado de Uruguay en Juegos Ol\u00edmpicos |author= |date=16 July 2008 |work=Terra |publisher= |accessdate=10 July 2012|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n;Olympic Games\n*[[Sailing at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Laser class|2004]]: 34th\n*[[Sailing at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's Laser class|2008]]: 17th\n*[[Sailing at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's Laser class|2012]]: 8th\n*[[Sailing at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Finn|2016]]: 19th\n\n;Pan American Games\n*[[Sailing at the 2007 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's Laser class|2007]]: ?\n*[[Sailing at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's Laser class|2011]]: 4th\n\n;ISAF Sailing World Championships\n*[[2007 ISAF Sailing World Championships|2007]]: 18th<ref>[http://www.sailing.org/2007-ISAF-Worlds.php?rgtaid=9066&evntid=13428&nocache=1#results ISAF Sailing World Championships 2007]</ref>\n*[[2011 ISAF Sailing World Championships|2011]]: [[2011 ISAF Sailing World Championships \u2013 Laser|52nd]]\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is brother of [[Andrea Foglia]] another [[Uruguay]]an [[sailor]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{World Sailing|359921|URUAF9|Alejandro Foglia Costa}}\n*{{IOC profile|alejandro-foglia-costa|Alejandro Foglia Costa}}\n*{{Olympic Channel|alejandro-foglia}}\n*{{SR/Olympics profile|fo/alejandro-foglia-1}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-sports|oly}}\n{{succession box\n| before = [[Serrana Fern\u00e1ndez]]\n| title = [[List of flag bearers for Uruguay at the Olympics|Flagbearer]] for {{URU}}\n| years = [[2008 Summer Olympics|Beijing 2008]]\n| after = [[Rodolfo Collazo]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Foglia, Alejandro}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Montevideo]]\n[[Category:Uruguayan male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2007 Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2011 Pan American Games]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Laser]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Laser]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Laser]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Finn]]\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of Uruguay]]\n[[Category:Pan American Games competitors for Uruguay]]\n[[Category:Uruguayan people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Snipe class sailors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n| name = Alejandro Foglia\n| full_name = Alejandro Jos\u00e9 Foglia Costa\n| birth_date = {{Birth-date and age|30 January 1984}}\n| birth_place = [[Montevideo]], Uruguay\n| height = 188 cm\n| weight = {{convert|13|st|kg}} \n| club = Yacht Club Punta del Este\n}}\n\n'''Alejandro Jos\u00e9 Foglia Costa'''{{efn Spanish name|Foglia|Costa}} (born 30 January 1984 in [[Montevideo]]) is a [[Uruguay]]an [[sailor]] in the [[Laser (dinghy)|Laser]] and [[Finn (dinghy)|Finn]] classes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.observa.com.uy/osecciones/especiales2/nota.aspx?id=114322 |title=Alejandro Foglia |date=28 June 2008 |work=Observa |accessdate=10 July 2012 |language=Spanish |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100421164801/http://www.observa.com.uy/osecciones/especiales2/nota.aspx?id=114322 |archivedate=21 April 2010 }}</ref>\n\nHe competed in four [[Summer Olympics]] for his native [[South America]]n country: [[Sailing at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Laser class|2004]], [[Sailing at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's Laser class|2008]], [[Sailing at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's Laser class|2012]] and [[Sailing at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Finn|2016]], and in two [[Pan American Games]]: [[Sailing at the 2007 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's Laser class|2007]] and [[Sailing at the 2011 Pan American Games \u2013 Men's Laser class|2011]].\n\nHe was named Uruguay's [[flagbearer]] for the [[2008 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deportesar.terra.com.ar/pekin2008/interna/0,,OI3012303-EI10485,00.html |title=Regatista Alejandro Foglia ser\u00e1 el abanderado de Uruguay en Juegos Ol\u00edmpicos |author= |date=16 July 2008 |work=Terra |publisher= |accessdate=10 July 2012|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n;Olympic Games\n*[[Sailing at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Laser class|2004]]: 34th\n*[[Sailing