868/20000211/tlc.jhtml | title = TLC Nominated For Three Soul Train Music Awards | publisher = [[MTV]] | date = February 11, 2000 | accessdate = July 4, 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"2000soultrainbillboard\">{{cite book | author = Gail Mitchell | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=nA4EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA10&dq=soul%20train%20music%20awards%2014th&pg=PA20#v=onepage&q&f=false | title = TLC Rides Soul Train | publisher = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date = March 18, 2000 | accessdate = July 4, 2010}}</ref> || {{nom}}\n|-\n| ''My Love Is Your Love'' || [[Soul Train Music Award for Best R&B/Soul Album, Female|Best R&B/Soul Album, Female]]<ref name=\"2000soultrain\"/><ref name=\"2000soultrainbillboard\"/>\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Artistic Achievement Award || [[Soul Train Music Awards#Show history|The Artist of the Decade \u2014 Female]]<ref name=\"2000soultrain\"/><ref name=\"2000soultrainbillboard\"/> || {{won}}\n|-\n{{End}}\n\n====''Billboard'' Magazine Year-End Charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=\"35\"|Year\n!width=\"340\"|Category\n!width=\"340\"|Work\n!width=\"75\"|Position\n|-\n| align=\"center\" rowspan=\"40\"|1999\n| Top Pop Artists<ref>{{cite book | author = | url = https://books.google.com/?id=9w0EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=RA1-PA4-IA24#v=onepage&q&f=false | title = ''Billboard'' 1999 The Year in Music, Year-End chart: the listing of Top Pop Artists | publisher = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date = December 25, 1999 | accessdate = August 26, 2010}}</ref>\n| six charted singles & albums\n| align=\"center\"|#9\n|-\n| Top ''Billboard'' 200 Album Artists<ref>{{cite book | author = | url = https://books.google.com/?id=9w0EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PP1&pg=RA1-PA4-IA25#v=onepage&q&f=false | title = ''Billboard'' 1999 The Year in Music, Year-End chart: the listing of Top ''Billboard'' 200 Album Artists | publisher = [[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date = December 25, 1999 | accessdate = August 26, 2010}}</ref>\n| one charted albums\n| align=\"center\"|#32\n|-\n| Top ''Billboa