017) 4.0%&nbsp;(2018)\n*2.6%&nbsp;(2019e) 3.2%&nbsp;(2020f)<ref name=\" World Bank\">{{cite web |url=https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/bitstream/handle/10986/33044/9781464814693.pdf |title=Global Economic Prospects, January 2020 : Slow Growth, Policy Challenges |page=101 |publisher=[[World Bank]] |website=openknowledge.worldbank.org |access-date=12 January 2020}}</ref>}}\n| per capita = {{plainlist|\n*{{increase}} $7,047 (nominal, 2019 est.)<ref name=\"IMFPeru\"/>\n*{{increase}} $14,719 (PPP, 2019 est.)<ref name=\"IMFPeru\"/>}}\n| per capita rank = {{plainlist|\n*[[List of countries by GDP (nominal) per capita|83rd (nominal, 2019)]]\n*[[List of countries by GDP (PPP) per capita|87th (PPP, 2019)]]}}\n| sectors = {{plainlist|\n*[[Primary sector of the economy|agriculture]]: 7.6%\n*[[Secondary sector of the economy|industry]]: 32.7%\n*[[Tertiary sector of the economy|services]]: 59.9% \n*(2017 est.)<ref name=\"CIA World Factbook Peru\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/resources/the-world-factbook/geos/pe.html|title=CIA World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency]] |access-date=2 January 2019}}</ref>}}\n| components = \n| inflation = 1.9% (2020 est.)<ref name=\"IMFPeru\"/>\n| poverty = {{plainlist|\n*{{decreasePositive}} 12.7% in [[Multidimensional Poverty Index|multidimensional poverty]] (2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gestion.pe/peru/peru-pais-mayor-reduccion-pobreza-multidimensional-ultima-decada-272889-noticia/|title=Per\u00fa fue el pa\u00eds con mayor reducci\u00f3n de la pobreza multidimensional en la \u00faltima d\u00e9cada|last=Gesti\u00f3n|first=Redacci\u00f3n|date=2019-07-11|website=Gesti\u00f3n|language=es|access-date=2020-02-02}}</ref>\n*{{decreasePositive}} 20.5% (2018)<ref>{{cite web|title=Peru {{!}} Data|url=https://data.worldbank.org/country/peru|website=[[World Bank]]|accessdate=16 April 2018|language=en-us}}</ref>\n*{{decreasePositive}} 22.1% on less than $5.50/day (2018)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://data.worldba